Name: granule_uid
Description: Unique ID in the data service of a coronal hole detection

Name: granule_gid
Description: Common ID to granules of same coronal hole

Name: obs_id
Description: Associates granules derived from the same observation

Name: dataproduct_type
Description: Organization of the data product, from enumerated list

Name: target_name
Description: Standard IAU name of target

Name: target_class
Description: Type of target

Name: time_min
Description: Start time (in JD) UTC measured at time_origin location

Name: time_max
Description: Stop time (in JD) UTC measured at time_origin location

Name: spectral_range_min
Description: Min spectral range (as frequency) of the observation

Name: spectral_range_max
Description: Max spectral range (as frequency) of the observation

Name: c1min
Description: Min helioprojective longitude of bounding box

Name: c1max
Description: Max helioprojective longitude of bounding box

Name: c2min
Description: Min helioprojective latitude of bounding box

Name: c2max
Description: Max helioprojective latitude of bounding box

Name: spatial_frame_type
Description: Flavor of coordinate system, defines the nature of coordinates

Name: instrument_host_name
Description: Standard name of the spacecraft

Name: instrument_name
Description: Standard name of instrument

Name: processing_level
Description: Simplified CODMAC calibration level

Name: processing_level_desc
Description: Describes specificities of the processing level

Name: creation_date
Description: Date of first entry of this granule

Name: modification_date
Description: Date of last modification

Name: release_date
Description: Start of public access period

Name: service_title
Description: Title of resource

Name: access_url
Description: URL of the data file

Name: access_format
Description: RFC 2045 media type (mime)

Name: access_estsize
Description: Estimate file size in kbyte

Name: thumbnail_url
Description: URL of a thumbnail image

Name: datalink_url
Description: Provides links to files or services on the server

Name: target_region
Description: Type of region or feature of interest

Name: feature_name
Description: Standard name of a region of interest

Name: publisher
Description: Resource publisher

Name: spatial_coordinate_description
Description: ID of specific coordinate system and version / properties

Name: spatial_origin
Description: Defines the frame origin

Name: time_scale
Description: Always UTC in data services

Name: target_distance_min
Description: Min observer-target distance

Name: target_distance_max
Description: Max observer-target distance

Name: observer_lon
Description: Observer's heliographic longitude

Name: observer_lat
Description: Observer's heliographic latitude

Name: ch_c1_centroid
Description: Helioprojective longitude of the centroid of the coronal hole

Name: ch_c2_centroid
Description: Helioprojective latitude of the centroid of the coronal hole

Name: ch_area_projected
Description: Area of the coronal hole as seen by the observer

Name: ch_area_projected_error
Description: Uncertainety of the area of the coronal hole as seen by the observer

Name: ch_area_deprojected
Description: Estimation of the area of the coronal hole on the solar photosphere

Name: ch_area_deprojected_error
Description: Uncertainety of the estimation of the area of the coronal hole on the solar photosphere

Name: ch_area_pixels
Description: Number of pixels of the cornal hole in the map

Name: ch_stat_aia_image
Description: Image onto which the cornal hole statistics are computed

Name: ch_stat_aia_sample_size
Description: Number of pixels of the cornal hole used to compute the statistics, the statistics are computed up to 0.95 solar radius

Name: ch_stat_aia_max
Description: Maximum of pixels values of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_aia_min
Description: Minimum of pixels values of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_aia_median
Description: Median of pixels values of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_aia_mean
Description: Mean of pixels values of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_aia_variance
Description: Variance of pixels values of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_aia_skewness
Description: Skewness of pixels values of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_aia_kurtosis
Description: Kurtosis of pixels values of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_aia_first_quartile
Description: First quartile of pixels values of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_aia_third_quartile
Description: Third quartile of pixels values of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_hmi_image
Description: Image onto which the cornal hole statistics are computed

Name: ch_stat_hmi_sample_size
Description: Number of pixels of the cornal hole used to compute the statistics, the statistics are computed up to 0.95 solar radius

Name: ch_stat_hmi_max
Description: Maximum of the magnetic field of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_hmi_min
Description: Minimum of the magnetic field of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_hmi_median
Description: Median of the magnetic field of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_hmi_mean
Description: Mean of the magnetic field of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_hmi_variance
Description: Variance of the magnetic field of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_hmi_skewness
Description: Skewness of the magnetic field of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_hmi_kurtosis
Description: Kurtosis of the magnetic field of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_hmi_first_quartile
Description: First quartile of the magnetic field of the cornal hole

Name: ch_stat_hmi_third_quartile
